{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0c75491-05f5-4a72-9940-8b980526da80","content":"There's no existing pipeline in this directory, so here's a general guide for the migration:\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** — Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test`, not the VSTest task.\n\n2. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n3. **TRX reports** — add the `--results-directory` and TRX logger:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n     displayName: 'Run Tests'\n     inputs:\n       command: test\n       arguments: >\n         --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n         --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n         --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n   ```\n\n4. **Publish results** — replace the implicit VSTest publishing:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n       searchFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n     condition: always()\n\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n     condition: always()\n   ```\n\n5. For **Cobertura** coverage format (needed by the publish task), add the coverlet collector or use:\n   ```\n   --collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"\n   ```\n\n### Summary of what's removed\n- `VSTest@3` task — no longer needed\n- Test platform auto-discovery — the test app is now self-contained\n\n### What stays the same\n- `PublishTestResults@2` still consumes `.trx` files\n- `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` still works for coverage\n\nUse `condition: always()` on the publish tasks so results are uploaded even on test failure.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e1374d1e-2565-4b09-b316-254f1145ea47","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no existing pipeline file. The user is asking a general question about how to migrate from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":611,"requestId":"0828:1E7A6A:82FA7D4:911ECF8:69EABE74"},"id":"b1790a3d-5aa2-4e55-ad16-226785df177a","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:12.851Z","parentId":"99c0332b-b163-4860-a3d4-91917a5876b2"}
